<task id="018" project="spaarke-daily-update-service-r2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Replace LegalWorkspace `dailyBriefing` registration with thin shim</title>
    <phase>P2: Pattern D Hoist</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>016</dependencies>
    <blocks>062</blocks>
    <tags>frontend, react, refactoring, fluent-ui</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Restructures SpaarkeAi mount path; must preserve P1 seam wiring</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Replace the static `dailyBriefingRegistration` in `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/dailyBriefing/` with a thin shim that consumes the factory from `@spaarke/daily-briefing-components`. Mirror the 62-line Calendar shim at `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/calendar.registration.ts`. The shim passes through `loadSpaarkeAiNotificationContext` from SpaarkeAi (wired in task 002) so SpaarkeAi continues to render real notifications.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in LegalWorkspace section-shim pattern (Calendar precedent) and SpaarkeAi composition.</role>

  <goal>LegalWorkspace section shim is ≤80 lines; consumes the new package's factory; SpaarkeAi continues to render real notifications via the shim path.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec design constraint and the calendar precedent: section-registration shims in LegalWorkspace are thin pass-throughs. After this task, the SpaarkeAi mount goes through the shim → new package factory → DailyBriefingApp.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/dailyBriefing/</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/calendar.registration.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/main.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Shim is a thin pass-through; no business logic; consumes shared package factory.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Must preserve P1 seam: `loadSpaarkeAiNotificationContext` injection from SpaarkeAi `main.tsx` continues to flow through.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-012-shared-component-library.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r2/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/calendar.registration.ts</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="LegalWorkspace section shim" location="src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/calendar.registration.ts">
        Calendar shim — 62 lines, thin pass-through. Mirror this shape.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `calendar.registration.ts` as the precedent shape.</step>
    <step order="2">Author `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/dailyBriefing/dailyBriefing.registration.ts` (or replace the existing file) as a thin shim.</step>
    <step order="3">Shim imports the factory from `@spaarke/daily-briefing-components` and wraps it with the LegalWorkspace section registration API.</step>
    <step order="4">Shim passes through the optional `loadNotificationContext` arg so SpaarkeAi's `main.tsx` injection continues to flow.</step>
    <step order="5">Delete any business logic or component code that was in the old registration location.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify build green on LegalWorkspace + SpaarkeAi + standalone code page.</step>
    <step order="7">Smoke test: cold-load SpaarkeAi workspace pane; Daily Briefing renders real notifications (P1 seam preserved).</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task 018 status from 🔲 to ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Build + dev server.</tool>
  </tools>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="SpaarkeAi mount path post-shim refactor">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={spaarke-ai-app-id}&amp;pagetype=custom&amp;name=sprk_spaarkeai</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Cold-load SpaarkeAi workspace as user with N&gt;0 unread notifications</step>
        <step>Open Daily Briefing pane</step>
        <step>Verify TL;DR + bullets render</step>
        <step>Verify P1 seam preserved (notifications match underlying `appnotification` rows)</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Real notifications render; P1 fix preserved</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/dailyBriefing/dailyBriefing.registration.ts</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">LegalWorkspace dailyBriefing registration is a thin shim (≤80 lines, no business logic).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Shim consumes `@spaarke/daily-briefing-components` factory.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">SpaarkeAi cold-load still renders real notifications (P1 seam preserved).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Don't touch `MicrosoftToDoIcon`, `authInit`, `runtimeConfig` here — those are DD tasks (050, 054, 055).
